Text.Value: I am the only one denied my claim.
The zaith'isk is working as intended.
Brace your mind, Lae'zel.Vlaakith tavki na'zin. Vlaakith tavki na'zin...
Focus your mind. Try to overload the device.
Your zaith'isk tried to kill Lae'zel. And failed.
The cure! Vlaakith m' zath'ak, isk'a'zaith!

EditorData.NodeContext: In great pain, still exclaiming/praying to Vlaakith. VLAH-kith mm zah-THOCK, isk-ah-ZAYTH! Abomination to Vlaakith, be purified!

Text.Value: I have done Vlaakith's will. I will be rewarded. I must.
Go on, into the zaith'isk. I will follow.
*The pain is too great. The visions flicker but refuse to come into focus.*
*Lae'zel's life is laid bare among those that came before. Her thoughts are turned to silver thread and relayed to the Astral Sea.*
Lies! Vlaakith, my Queen - COMPLETE ME!
Damn it all, the parasite. I still feel it.
Draw on the zaith'isk's power, take it as your own.
Make way, Lae'zel. I am purging myself of this damned parasite.
I am disappointed that we could not extract it alive. It would have been an exceptional specimen.
Really? Then - all this destruction was a symptom of its power... Incredible.
In any case, the problem is resolved. Leave me. I must salvage what I can.
Hshar'lak. I will enjoy this.
Betrayer. I will enjoy this.
Extract yourself. Mother Gith would not wish you to suffer.
Praise Vlaakith, let it be done.
Get her away from that thing - now!
And yet she lives, and so does her parasite.
Nnngh!
I will not. I gave you my might. You will respect my charge.
Yes. Yes! Relieve me, Vlaakith!
I feel it. Skin stretching. Mind failing. NGH!

EditorData.NodeContext: Lae'zel in great pain but pushing through.

Text.Value: Go ahead, Lae'zel. You've earned it.
You wouldn't dare! I -

EditorData.NodeContext: Worked up for a moment before reasliing the player is trying to get her to calm down

Text.Value: Examine the device.
My Queen, hear me!
I've seen the truth, Lae'zel. This device doesn't cure - it kills.

Text.Value: I hear you and I deny you. Your turn will come.
Wait and watch.
Purification is my right. I AM GITHYANKI. I WILL NOT BE GHAIK!

The 'head' part of the machine descends and the jaws clamp around the Laezel's head, neck, shoulders.

Text.Value: Yes, child! Face her will!
No! No!
Call on your parasite. Show Lae'zel what she stands to lose.
I have ably commanded this party. I will be cleansed first.
You would still be hunting for this place without my guidance. I will be cured first.
My life's work... gone.
Do not patronise me. Purity is Vlaakith's promise. This was the way.
Lies! Vlaakith, my Queen - COMPLETE ME!
What madness is this? The zaith'isk nearly destroyed me!
Wait and watch.
*The device is an ingenious synthesis of illithid anatomy and metal alloys. It hums with psionic energy, hinting at paths into unknown minds and unseen planes.*
Yes, child. Speak the Tla'ket. Meditate on its verses.
*The zaith'isk's psionic forces batter Lae'zel's thoughts. There is no chance she will survive this unscathed.*
*The many planes of existence stretch before you, then coalesce. You are gifted, you are cursed.*

Text.Value: That thing's killing her. Do something, damn it!
*Your thoughts weave through the zaith'isk's psionic pathways, turning its own power against it.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [PLYR] Having a mindmeld of intense pain, plyr tries to focus his mind on the machine. Show plyr in a pose that is trying to control the machine. <Gwen Lee>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player squints hard, trying to overload the zaith'isk. The head of the zaith'isk lifts from Lae'zel's.

Text.Value: Our duty to Vlaakith remains. Control your emotion, let our queen be our focus.
MY QUEEN! MAKE ME WHOLE!
No! Vlaakith, purge me of this blight!
Wait and watch.
*An ulitharid skull, refashioned for cleansing - the zaith'isk. Purity at long last.*
*The device is strange, made of taut flesh and pockmarked metal. It waits for something.*
Get out of there, Lae'zel. You won't survive this anguish.
Mother Gith is sovereign no longer!
We must extract it as soon as possible.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: She's going to call the guards to kill you, but doesn't want to tip you off.

Text.Value: REMOVE HER.
REMOVE HER.
REMOVE HER.
REMOVE HER.
REMOVE HER.
REMOVE HER.

Text.Value: That thing's killing her!
*The zaith'isk overwhelms the both of you. The weight of the astral sea crushes your mind and spirit.*
*The ruined device stands inert, chilling the air around it.*
ROAR!

Text.Value: Let this be a beginning, not an end.
Take heart. We'll find a way.
...Vlaakith'ka sivim hrath krash'ht!
You walk the line between confident and arrogant. A beguiling turn of events.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Zaith'isk] Animation of the machine's head in an unstable state and its tubes and mandibles jittering in a fast speed. Laezel is still in agony.  Intensity:3  <Gwen Lee>

Text.Value: *Your marrow quakes within your bones. Behind the pain, a new sensation rises: power.*
*An unseen blade cleaves your mind in two. Impossible pain sears your bones and body in concert with Lae'zel's.*

Text.Value: And it destroyed a zaith'isk... Then its power is even more unique than I thought. I must examine it.
Listen to me. I see your flesh pulsing. The zaith'isk will make you ghaik!
You must listen! The device is changing you. You are becoming illithid.
*The device is part organic, part synthetic. But you can't tell how it was made, or how it works.*
*You feel Lae'zel's mind rip and rupture. Is this purification? Is this the cure?*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Show Laezel turning into a braindead zombie

Text.Value: That thing looks set to kill her!
Wait here. I will gather my tools.

EditorData.NodeContext: She's lying - she's going to call the guards

Text.Value: Leave.
Pursue the visions you saw. See where they lead.
Your tadpole is changing, growing. You have to resist the machine!
Lash'a'kla! Lash'a'kla! Lash'a'kla!

EditorData.NodeContext: Lae'zel in absolute torture.  lahsh-ah-KLAH! Make me pure!

Text.Value: And I'm done with you. Good riddance.

Text.Value: It saved her?
I am becoming pure!
You're lying. You're protecting it. I knew it - the parasite's influence has grown. It has changed her, changed you.
The only variable in this experience was you - and your parasite. And I will uncover how this happened.
Tsk'va - contempt for power, contempt for allegiance. I am done with you.
All right, all right. Go ahead.
*Your vision narrows. You sense myriad spectres of githyanki past. This is their fate. This is their anguish.*
Cry our queen's command. Lash'a'kla!
Abide the pain, Lae'zel. It is Vlaakith's will!
Embrace the pain, Lae'zel. Be pure.
Control your tongue, before I slice it out.

Text.Value: *The device is too powerful. You hold no sway over it.*
Keep focused, Lae'zel. The cure is close.
Back off, or I will personally present your head to Vlaakith.
Out of my way. Or would you rather I split you in two and walk through the centre?
So... we're just going to stand here and let it kill her? Is that the plan?
The parasite lives, yes. And thank goodness - it saved her.
Seek answers within the zaith'isk. What is this vision?
*There's something in her voice that goes beyond rage - curiosity, perhaps, or regret. Whatever it is, you cannot identify it.*
A persuasive argument, if not the most eloquent.
*Her voice cuts with a fanatical edge - an obsession bordering on mania. If there's a chance the parasite lives, she wants it.*
Stand back. I'm going first.
I must meditate. There is much to think on.
Sit, child. Let the zaith'isk end your suffering.
You are the infected one, child? Sit, ra'stil. Let the zaith'isk end your suffering.

EditorData.logicalname: Player said the cleansing was for a friend

Text.Value: I do so enjoy when you choose boldness over blandness.
Out of my head!
*You share in Lae'zel's agony. Every cell within her skull bursts into a constellation of fragments, sorted and reassembled. Lae'zel will die if she remains.*

I will not turn from my queen! EXALTED VLAAKITH. I AM RESTORED!
Ghustil, assist me. This one is Hshar'lak!

Text.Value: Calm down. You're not the only one infected, you know.

ENOUGH.
ENOUGH.
ENOUGH.
ENOUGH.
ENOUGH.
ENOUGH.

Synopsis: |COM branch for Laezel interacting with the Zaith'isk. She is convinced the machine is there to cure her and refuses to open her eyes to the reality that it's killing her. The player can intervene and stop it, or let it play out. Eventually, the device explodes and the doctor calls the guards.|
